The issue with the code is that the `InputStream.read` method is used to read the contents of the file, but it is not being passed to the `DiskFileItem` constructor. Instead, the `InputStream` should be passed to the `FileItemFactory.getItem` method.

Here's the corrected code:
```java
final File TEST_FILE = new File("C:/my_text.txt");
final DiskFileItemFactory factory = new DiskFileItemFactory();
final DiskFileItem diskFileItem = factory.getItem("fileData", "text/plain", true);
diskFileItem.setName(TEST_FILE.getName());
diskFileItem.setSize(TEST_FILE.length());
InputStream inputStream = new FileInputStream(TEST_FILE);
diskFileItem.setInputStream(inputStream);
inputStream.close();
System.out.println("diskFileItem.getString() = " + diskFileItem.getString());
```
This should correctly read the contents of the file and pass it to the `DiskFileItem`.
